citation.biblCit: Odynak, David, 2015, "University of Alberta Graduand Survey, 1992", https://doi.org/10.7939/DVN/10588, UAL Dataverse, V2

stdyInfo.abstract: The 1992 Graduand Survey was undertaken to assist the University of Alberta in its efforts to improve the quality of education received by students. The survey was conducted in June 1992 in conjunction with the University of Alberta's spring Convocation.

sumDscr.geogCover: Alberta, City of Edmonton, University of Alberta
sumDscr.universe: All students graduating from undergraduate or professional programs were surveyed, and completed questionnaires were received from 1460 graduands (34 percent of those graduating). Respondents appeared to be typical of the population of graduands although women were somewhat more likely to respond. This bias was taken into account in data analyses by comparing responses by gender.

othrStdyMat.relMat: Krahn, Harvey, and Brian J. Silzer. "A Study Of Exit Surveys: The Graduand Survey At The University Of Alberta." College And University 71.1 (1995): 12-23. ERIC.
